00:56.722 --> 01:00.659
Ma, this Turkey
is sensational.
Mm-hmm.

01:00.726 --> 01:02.627
Mmm.

01:02.695 --> 01:05.429
Gloria, I love your stuffing.

01:13.539 --> 01:15.540
[ Loud sigh ]

01:18.544 --> 01:20.545
What was that for?

01:20.612 --> 01:23.614
What, Archie?
What was that for?

01:23.683 --> 01:26.851
No. I didn't mean "what"
meaning what did you say.

01:26.919 --> 01:29.253
I meant what meaning
what was "what" for?

01:33.759 --> 01:37.428
What other "what"
was there, Edith?
You sighed.

01:37.496 --> 01:39.164
Did I sigh?

01:39.231 --> 01:42.734
Yeah, you sighed,
and you heaved it right over
in this direction.

01:46.839 --> 01:49.240
It's like trying to eat
in a wind tunnel.

01:51.243 --> 01:55.580
Well, I'm sorry. I must have
done it "unconscious."

01:55.647 --> 01:57.982
That's the way you go
through life, Edith.

02:05.624 --> 02:08.059
[ Sighs ]
Now cut that out!

02:08.127 --> 02:11.295
<i>Now, daddy, be nice.</i>
<i>It's Christmas.</i>

02:11.363 --> 02:14.866
That's what "what" was for.

02:14.934 --> 02:19.503
I guess I sighed because
somehow it just don't seem
like Christmas.

02:19.571 --> 02:22.974
- I know what you mean, ma.
- What do you mean
you know what she means?

02:23.042 --> 02:26.945
Nothing. I was going to say
that mom means that we're all
kowtowing to Madison Avenue...

02:27.012 --> 02:29.180
And the almighty
cash register.
<i>[ Archie scoffing ]</i>

02:29.248 --> 02:32.416
Yeah, she means that
Christmas has been
exploited by big business.

02:32.484 --> 02:34.719
It's a victim
of crass commercialism.

02:34.787 --> 02:37.956
Oh, my. Did I mean all that?

02:40.760 --> 02:44.262
You know, Michael's right.
Christmas is never like
what you read about.

02:44.329 --> 02:48.099
Nobody ever sits around
the fire roasting chestnuts
and telling ghost stories.

02:48.167 --> 02:54.005
Maybe that's it, Archie.
We got no chestnuts
roasting on the fire.

02:55.440 --> 02:57.942
Edith, how long
we been living
in this here house?

02:58.010 --> 03:00.178
Twenty years.
Twenty years.

03:00.246 --> 03:03.581
In all them 20 years,
you ever happen to notice
any fireplaces anywhere?

03:06.385 --> 03:08.887
No.
[ Mocking ]
No.

03:08.954 --> 03:12.123
So maybe that's why
we don't have chestnuts, huh?

03:12.191 --> 03:15.193
'Cause the house
happens to be heated
by radiators.

03:15.261 --> 03:21.099
That's right, Archie.
And "radiated" chestnuts
wouldn't be the same.

03:25.271 --> 03:29.274
But it ain't just the nuts.
It's the bubble.

03:29.341 --> 03:33.878
Huh?
Ah, geez.
The bubbles are missing.

03:33.946 --> 03:37.816
I think what ma's trying
to say is you're not your gay,
bubbly, christmassy self, daddy.

03:37.883 --> 03:41.652
I am gay. I'm gay.
I'm as gay
as everybody here!

03:43.322 --> 03:46.257
Gee, you sure coulda
fooled me.

03:46.325 --> 03:51.162
What's the matter, Archie?
You're acting like you're giving
up on Christmas this year.

03:51.230 --> 03:54.098
Why you so down?
Where's your Christmas spirit?

03:54.166 --> 03:58.002
What do you mean?
Who do you think hung
the wreath on the door, huh?

03:58.070 --> 04:01.239
One of "santee's go-nomes"?

04:01.307 --> 04:04.309
Don't be telling me
I'm down, huh?

04:04.376 --> 04:07.045
Well, maybe down
isn't the right word.

04:07.112 --> 04:10.781
Maybe it's--
maybe it's more like low.

04:10.850 --> 04:13.852
Like this tree
you bought.

04:17.322 --> 04:20.992
What's the matter
with the tree?
Archie, look at it.

04:21.060 --> 04:23.561
It's not exactly
the king of the forest.

04:24.363 --> 04:26.597
Yeah, or even a prince.

04:26.665 --> 04:30.235
There ain't nothing the matter
with this tree a little
decorating wouldn't help.

04:30.302 --> 04:32.503
How come nobody put
the star on it this year?

04:32.571 --> 04:35.073
I tried, Archie.

04:35.140 --> 04:39.810
But every time I put
the star on,
the tree fell over.

04:39.879 --> 04:42.546
I don't care
nothing about that.

04:42.614 --> 04:46.617
I wasn't laying out
no 20-30 bucks
for a big tree.

04:46.685 --> 04:50.788
Maybe if my firm would give out
their Christmas bonus as usual,

04:50.856 --> 04:53.358
well, then I'd have
laid out big, as usual.

04:53.425 --> 04:57.828
But they didn't.
They're cutting back.
There was no bonus, nothing.

04:57.897 --> 05:00.531
Gee, you really are down.

05:00.599 --> 05:03.601
I ain't down!
I'm up, up, up.

05:03.668 --> 05:06.004
Who was the first
to yell "merry Christmas"
this morning?

05:06.071 --> 05:10.909
- Michael was.
- Oh, all right.
I was next then, eh?

05:10.976 --> 05:14.312
Geez. And didn't I
bring your coffee
up to bed,

05:14.380 --> 05:17.382
like I do
every Christmas morning?
Yeah, Archie.

05:17.449 --> 05:20.118
All right.
That shows you I ain't down.

05:20.185 --> 05:23.687
You gotta be up to remember
to do a thing like that
once a year.

05:26.392 --> 05:30.228
Well, Archie, something must be
bothering you, otherwise
you wouldn't be in such a mood.

05:30.296 --> 05:33.064
I am not in no mood.

05:33.132 --> 05:36.167
Oh, gee, daddy.
You didn't even join in
the bunker glee club this year.

05:36.235 --> 05:39.603
- Aw, the bunker glee club.
- Yeah, you didn't do
your fa-la-la's.

05:39.671 --> 05:44.909
I fa-la-la'd in the kitchen.
Maybe you didn't hear me.

05:44.977 --> 05:47.545
Let's do it again,
and we'll hear you this time.
Yeah, let's go.

05:47.612 --> 05:49.780
Leave me alone, will ya?
Get outta here.
Come on. Let's go.

05:49.848 --> 05:52.850
Okay.
[ All ] ¶ deck the halls
with boughs of holly ¶

05:52.918 --> 05:57.855
- ¶ fa-la-la-la-la ¶
- ¶ la-la-la-la ¶

05:57.923 --> 06:01.592
¶ 'tis the season to be jolly
fa-la-la-la-la ¶

06:01.660 --> 06:04.228
¶ la-la-la-la ¶
will ya?

06:04.296 --> 06:07.631
Now, that showed
I ain't down, huh? I'm up.

06:07.699 --> 06:11.402
Just leave me alone, will ya?
Let me digest my dinner.
<i>¶ [ Carolers singing ]</i>

06:11.470 --> 06:14.638
Hey, it's carolers.
Look, right on the front porch.
<i>¶ [ Singing continues ]</i>

06:14.706 --> 06:19.810
Wow,
don't they sound great?
Oh, my. They look so sweet.

06:19.878 --> 06:22.847
They've been torturing us
with that racket for three days.

06:22.914 --> 06:26.417
- I'm gonna give 'em something.
- Look at Edith,
runnin' me into bankruptcy,

06:26.485 --> 06:28.886
feeding them panhandlers.

06:30.489 --> 06:33.157
