a merry Christmas ¶
very good. We enjoyed it.

06:33.225 --> 06:36.260
[ All saying thank you ]
<i>[ Mike ]</i>
<i>Merry Christmas.</i>

06:36.328 --> 06:40.831
Oh, my.
Wasn't that nice, Archie?

06:40.899 --> 06:43.734
I call it
disturbing the peace.

06:43.802 --> 06:49.474
I am sick of people wishing me
merry Christmas whilst
they're picking my pocket.

06:49.541 --> 06:54.145
I never saw you
sick of Christmas before.

06:54.213 --> 06:56.381
Yeah, daddy. You always
liked Christmas Carols.

06:56.448 --> 06:58.949
Everybody likes
Christmas Carols.

06:59.018 --> 07:03.888
You know, I remember when I was
a kid, my family used to sit
under the tree and sing Carols.

07:09.495 --> 07:12.263
Of course,
we always had a big tree.

07:12.331 --> 07:15.866
You always have
a big mouth too?

07:15.934 --> 07:20.104
Well, I mean, we didn't
buy our tree in a parking
lot from ferguson's supermarket.

07:20.172 --> 07:24.042
No. Our tree came down
on big trucks
all the way from Ontario.

07:24.109 --> 07:27.111
- Hey, what did you mean
by that?
- What'd I say?

07:27.179 --> 07:29.813
You know what you said, Ontario.
I don't know what
you're talking about.

07:29.881 --> 07:32.250
Don't be a wise guy.
You know what you mean.

07:32.317 --> 07:34.552
Archie, wait a second.
Ontario's a province
in Canada.

07:34.619 --> 07:38.289
Did you tell him
about Ontario?
I never said a word, Archie.

07:38.357 --> 07:40.591
- Daddy, what's your problem
with Ontario?
- She said it again.

07:40.659 --> 07:43.294
What are youse two
trying to pull anyway?
Nothing.

07:43.362 --> 07:46.030
Listen, Professor. Suppose
your bosses said to you,

07:46.098 --> 07:49.167
"get off a special shipment
right away to London," huh?

07:49.234 --> 07:51.602
What would you do?
Wait a second, Archie.
What are you talking about?

07:51.670 --> 07:54.172
You'd have sent it off
to London. You'd have sent it
off to London, england.

07:54.239 --> 07:56.907
Who the hell ever heard of
London, Ontario?

08:00.345 --> 08:02.813
I heard of London, Ontario.

08:02.881 --> 08:06.850
That is the stupidest thing
I ever heard of, naming two
places in the world the same.

08:06.918 --> 08:11.489
Archie, lots of places have
the same name. Like Odessa,
Russia and Odessa, Texas.

08:11.557 --> 08:14.024
Yeah. Birmingham, england;
Birmingham, Alabama.

08:14.093 --> 08:16.360
New York, New York.

08:20.632 --> 08:23.634
Will you stifle yourself.

08:25.837 --> 08:29.173
Now don't be talking
about that tree no more.
All right.

08:29.241 --> 08:31.909
I didn't see you
laying out any big dough
for Christmas cheer.

08:31.977 --> 08:37.548
Oh, Archie. What about that
lovely electric carving knife
they gave us?
[ Scoffs ]

08:37.616 --> 08:43.453
- What about the cigars?
- Cigars. Do you call
these things cigars here?

08:43.522 --> 08:48.025
When I smoke a cigar,
I wanna feel tobacco
between my teeth.

08:48.093 --> 08:51.095
Not one of these
plastic penny whistles.

08:53.232 --> 08:56.900
Yeah. I take two puffs
of these and I'm singeing
the hair inside my nose.

08:58.770 --> 09:01.872
Thanks a lot, daddy.
We happened to think
you might like a small cigar...

09:01.940 --> 09:03.874
For when you don't
have time to finish a big one.

09:03.942 --> 09:07.878
I always finish a big one.
Even if
it takes two weeks.

09:10.882 --> 09:13.050
Sweet tipparoos.

09:13.118 --> 09:16.987
They smell like they was
dipped in a can of flit.

09:17.055 --> 09:20.324
Archie, just because you're in
a bad mood you don't have
to say our presents stink.

09:20.392 --> 09:24.228
I never used the word stink.

09:24.296 --> 09:28.666
All I'm saying is that
Christmas presents, they
ought to be individual-like.

09:28.733 --> 09:30.734
Oh, you mean like
what you gave us?

09:30.802 --> 09:32.836
A box of
his-and-hers handkerchiefs.

09:32.904 --> 09:35.406
Listen, if you don't like 'em,
you can give 'em back.

09:35.474 --> 09:37.542
I told ya,
I didn't get
no bonus this year.

09:37.609 --> 09:42.613
It's the thought that matters.
I love my her handkerchiefs.

09:42.681 --> 09:45.916
How did you ever get 'em
to split a box?

09:45.984 --> 09:48.152
Aw, shush.

09:55.994 --> 09:59.997
I started talking about
individual presents.

10:00.065 --> 10:02.700
Like the time that
Gloria here was a little girl.

10:02.767 --> 10:06.770
And you wanted
a real China Dolly
and a Dollhouse.

10:06.838 --> 10:10.007
A real one.
I couldn't afford that.

10:10.075 --> 10:14.078
I was climbing the walls
trying to raise that money.
A buck here, a quarter there.

10:14.145 --> 10:17.815
Then just before Christmas,
the boss gave me my first bonus.

10:17.882 --> 10:21.552
You know, I coulda kissed
the guy. I ran outta there
faster than Jesse Owens.

10:21.620 --> 10:26.724
And I went out and bought you
the most beautiful China Dolly
and Dollhouse you ever seen.

10:26.791 --> 10:31.061
That's a lovely story, daddy.
But I don't remember that doll.

10:31.129 --> 10:34.465
That's 'cause
you never got it.
Hey, hey, hey.

10:36.801 --> 10:40.238
Your father had too much
to drink,
stifle yourself.

10:40.305 --> 10:43.140
And coming up the front steps
he tripped and fell.

10:43.208 --> 10:45.643
Will you stifle yourself.

10:45.711 --> 10:49.913
He wasn't hurt,
but the Dolly and house
was smashed to pieces.

10:49.981 --> 10:53.484
Why can't you stifle?
<i>[ Doorbell ringing ]</i>

10:53.552 --> 10:57.221
Get that, will ya, meathead?
'Cause I don't want
to look at nobody.

10:58.357 --> 11:01.158
Geez, you've got
a wicked memory.

11:01.226 --> 11:05.563
Merry Christmas, Mike.
Merry Christmas, everybody.

11:05.631 --> 11:09.967
Oh. Don't tell me
you're delivering milk
on Christmas day there, wilbur.

11:10.034 --> 11:12.236
Oh, no. This ain't
no delivery, Archie.

11:12.304 --> 11:17.341
Oh. Well, then, what could you
possibly be here for?

11:17.409 --> 11:20.478
Uh, well,
you see, Mrs. bunker,

11:20.545 --> 11:23.947
when I come by yesterday,
you was out.

11:24.015 --> 11:28.919
But I left the money for
our milk bill with Mrs. mcnab.
Didn't you get it?

11:28.987 --> 11:32.456
Oh yeah, I got <i>that</i> money.
[ Edith ]
Oh, good.

11:37.596 --> 11:40.063
Then what do you want?

11:41.800 --> 11:47.405
It's, uh, a little bit
embarrassing having to ask,
if you know what I mean.

11:47.472 --> 11:52.576
I know what he means.
I don't know
what he means.

11:52.644 --> 11:56.614
Well, you know, it's that time
of year, ain't it?

11:56.682 --> 11:58.683
When everybody's givin'.

11:58.750 --> 12:02.420
Who's givin' me? Nobody.
I'm one of the guys
that gets took.

12:02.487 --> 12:04.722
Nixon's worried about
wagin' price controls.

12:04.790 --> 12:07.325
When's he gonna stick out
a little tip control?

12:07.392 --> 12:11.462
I ain't asking for no raise.
Just the same tip as last year.

12:11.530 --> 12:15.032
Oh, that's nice, Archie,
ain't it?
<i>Yeah.</i>

12:15.099 --> 12:17.435
What a break for us, Edith.

12:17.502 --> 12:20.671
You're gonna think it's nice
when the two of us are going
over the hill to the poor house.

12:20.739 --> 12:23.140
[ Chuckles ]
That'll be the day.

12:23.208 --> 12:26.176
With the kind of bonuses
your firm handed out this week.

12:26.244 --> 12:31.248
Hey, wilbur, ain't your family
expectin' you home with them
on Christmas day?

12:31.316 --> 12:33.851
Wait a second.
Archie's firm gave out bonuses?

12:33.918 --> 12:37.187
Oh, yeah. Old man feeney
down the block told me
your boss...

12:37.255 --> 12:39.590
Come through this Christmas
as usual.

12:39.658 --> 12:42.159
Feeney's crazy.
There wasn't no bonus.

12:42.227 --> 12:45.295
Are you kiddin'? I seen
the new vacuum cleaner...

12:45.364 --> 12:48.031
Feeney bought his missus
with the bonus money.

12:48.099 --> 12:51.769
Well, happy holiday,
everybody.
Bye, wilbur.

12:53.972 --> 12:55.973
<i>[ Door closes ]</i>

13:00.645 --> 13:06.016
Now, who you gonna believe?
Me, or a big-mouth milkman?

13:13.024 --> 13:16.861
I'm tellin' ya, if feeney
got any extra money, it was
some back pay he had comin'...

13:16.928 --> 13:19.129
Because the firm
didn't give out no bonus.

13:19.197 --> 13:22.366
Well, then, why did wilbur
say that your boss came through
this year like he always does?

13:22.434 --> 13:26.003
Yeah. I wonder how
Mrs. feeney's enjoying
her new vacuum cleaner.

13:26.070 --> 13:29.072
Yeah, it's lucky for her
feeney got his bonus.

13:29.140 --> 13:32.976
Ma, you'd enjoy one of
those new cannister cleaners.
They're very powerful.

13:33.044 --> 13:38.215
Yeah. Great for picking up
big pine needles
from big Christmas trees.

13:40.852 --> 13:44.187
Stop it! Stop it,
both of you, this minute.

13:44.255 --> 13:47.758
If your father says
there was no bonus,
there was no bonus.

13:53.998 --> 13:58.569
Yeah. Why don't youse, uh,
go on, help your mother clear
off the table or something.

13:58.637 --> 14:00.805
Come on.

14:03.074 --> 14:07.411
<i>[ Carolers ]</i>
<i>¶ it came upon</i>
<i> </i> <i> a midnight clear ¶</i>

14:07.479 --> 14:10.648
aw, these singers
are going to drive me
out of my nut.

