a midnight clear ¶

15:18.149 --> 15:21.485
will you
stifle yourself, Edith.

15:21.553 --> 15:24.555
I mean, just for a change,
can we have a little
silent night around here?

15:24.623 --> 15:28.458
Oh, all right.
¶ silent night ¶
no, no. Edith.

15:30.361 --> 15:33.531
You're scrapin' a nerve.

15:33.598 --> 15:37.701
You know, I think when you was
a kid, somebody must have
dropped you on your throat.

15:41.540 --> 15:44.207
Oh, look at this
back here.

15:44.275 --> 15:46.777
<i>Hey, get out from under</i>
<i>the mistletoe.</i>
<i>You're making it droop.</i>

15:48.547 --> 15:50.548
Archie, will you
quit being so sore?

15:50.615 --> 15:53.751
Yeah, daddy, cheer up.
You're acting like scrooge.

15:53.818 --> 15:55.986
Aw, don't "scrooge" me.

15:56.054 --> 16:01.058
I'm the only one around here
that understands the true
and solemn meaning of Christmas.

16:01.125 --> 16:05.529
Which is a time for peace
and quiet "contemptation."

16:05.597 --> 16:10.100
Oh, but I think you're allowed
to be jolly too.

16:10.168 --> 16:14.504
Sure you can be jolly,
Edith. Just be jolly
with your mouth shut.

16:16.875 --> 16:20.210
Just sit there
and think.
Think what?

16:20.278 --> 16:25.282
Don't be a dingbat, will ya?
Think. Think
religious thoughts.

16:25.349 --> 16:27.818
Oh, drinking beer, daddy?
That's real religious.

16:27.886 --> 16:31.055
What's the matter with that?

16:31.122 --> 16:33.791
Geez, the Bible's full of wine.

16:33.858 --> 16:38.896
No, God don't have
nothing against taking a drink
to celebrate his son's birthday.

16:38.964 --> 16:43.100
Archie, there's no proof
that Jesus was God's son.
That's-that's fairy tales.

16:43.167 --> 16:46.336
Aw, come on,
you meatheaded atheist you.

16:48.006 --> 16:51.508
Gee. They don't give you
a holiday for fairy tales.

16:57.616 --> 17:01.451
All over the world
they celebrate the birth
of that baby.

17:01.519 --> 17:03.854
And everybody gets time off
from work.

17:03.922 --> 17:07.758
Now if that ain't proof
that he's the son of God,
then nothing is.

17:10.161 --> 17:14.498
Archie, I'm not saying that
a philosopher named Jesus
didn't live in those days.

17:14.565 --> 17:17.067
I'm saying there was
no proof that he was
the son of God.

17:17.135 --> 17:21.137
- Like I said, it's fairy tales.
- The Bible ain't fairy tales
there, meathead.

17:21.204 --> 17:23.573
The Bible is facts all the way,
right from the beginning...

17:23.642 --> 17:27.645
When God made the world
in seven days.
Six days, Archie.

17:27.712 --> 17:32.116
Seven days, Edith.
No. On the seventh day
he rested.

17:32.183 --> 17:34.184
Well, maybe half a day,
Edith,

17:34.252 --> 17:37.420
but the other half
he went around checking
on what he'd done.

17:42.260 --> 17:47.430
And he made us all
one true religion, Edith,
christians,

17:47.498 --> 17:49.499
which he named after
his son, Christian.

17:52.503 --> 17:55.005
Or Christ for short.

17:57.441 --> 18:01.879
I never thought of that.

18:01.946 --> 18:06.616
Certainly. That's the way
it was for a long time.
One religion.

18:06.685 --> 18:12.022
Till they started
splittin' off into all them
other "denumerations" there.

18:12.090 --> 18:15.592
Your catholics,
your "persbytarians."

18:15.660 --> 18:18.996
Lutherans, et cetera,
et cetera.

18:19.064 --> 18:23.533
But there's still only
one true religion to this day,
and that's his religion.

18:23.601 --> 18:26.236
Of course, that's the one
you belong to, right, arch?

18:26.304 --> 18:31.641
I'd be kind of stupid
if I didn't, wouldn't I?
[ Chuckles ]

18:31.710 --> 18:35.713
Yeah, I tell you.
My heart goes out
to a lot of guys I know.

18:35.780 --> 18:41.451
Yeah, they spend their lives
believin' one of them
offshoot religions, you know?

18:41.519 --> 18:45.355
Sendin' their kids to them
there. Givin' 'em money.

18:45.423 --> 18:48.926
Runnin' dances for them.
And then in the end
they get up there...

18:48.993 --> 18:52.495
And they find out
they was foolin' around
with the wrong one all along.

18:55.433 --> 18:58.268
That's sad, you know that?
<i>[ Doorbell ringing ]</i>

18:58.336 --> 19:01.471
Hold it. Hold it.
Hold it, everybody.
I'm gonna get that.

19:01.539 --> 19:04.875
There's gonna be
no more panhandlin'
from this door today.

19:20.558 --> 19:22.926
Who are you?

19:22.994 --> 19:25.796
It's me, Jefferson.

19:25.864 --> 19:28.498
Oh, geez.
Well, how was I
supposed to know that?

19:28.566 --> 19:32.736
It's Mr. Jefferson
dressed up like Santa.
Come in.

19:32.804 --> 19:35.806
Hold it. Hold it.
There's more of them here.

19:35.874 --> 19:39.877
[ All saying merry Christmas ]

19:39.944 --> 19:42.946
Oh, I hope we are not
interrupting anything.

19:43.014 --> 19:46.516
Oh, my, no.
You're very welcome.
[ Laughs ]

19:46.584 --> 19:50.587
So you're supposed to be
Santa claus, are you?

19:50.655 --> 19:53.157
Ho, ho, ho.

19:59.664 --> 20:03.333
You look more like
a rabbi to me.

20:08.372 --> 20:12.209
Oh, Henry is playing Santa
down at the youth center.

20:12.277 --> 20:16.446
So we thought we'd drop by
on our way and leave this off.

20:16.514 --> 20:21.785
I baked it myself.
Oh, look, Archie.
A lovely fruitcake.

20:21.853 --> 20:25.555
Much obliged, Mrs. j.
Thank you, Louise.

20:25.623 --> 20:28.658
Come on. Have some eggnog.
Look, Gloria.
Oh.

20:28.726 --> 20:31.895
I see you go for
the latest thing
in Christmas trees.

20:33.531 --> 20:37.667
Huh?
Yeah, the Japanese
dwarf species.

20:39.337 --> 20:42.505
[ Mike ] Mr. Jefferson,
you want some eggnog?
Sure would. Thank you.

20:42.573 --> 20:47.410
I hope it's not
too strong for ya.
Merry Christmas, neighbors.

20:47.478 --> 20:50.047
[ All ]
Merry Christmas.

20:50.114 --> 20:52.549
Oh, this is great eggnog,
Mr. bunker.

20:52.616 --> 20:56.453
You ain't just
whistlin' Dixie there, Lionel.
Oh, I never do that.

20:58.656 --> 21:02.993
Well, let's everybody
sit down and we'll have
a nice visit.

21:03.061 --> 21:05.395
Yeah, yeah.
Come on. Come on.
Sit down, all of youse.

21:05.463 --> 21:09.632
As long as youse are here
you might as well--
but not in my-- aw!

21:12.303 --> 21:16.974
Is that a new coat,
Louise?
Yes, isn't it beautiful?

21:17.041 --> 21:19.209
George gave it to me
for Christmas.
Oh.

21:19.277 --> 21:21.879
I ain't seen your husband George
since you moved in there.

21:21.946 --> 21:26.283
- What's he doing with himself?
- Well, he's home watching
the new tv we gave him.

21:26.351 --> 21:29.519
[ Edith ]
It sounds like you're having
a wonderful Christmas.

21:29.587 --> 21:32.256
[ Louise ]
We are.
And how did you do, Edith?

21:32.323 --> 21:36.226
Oh, well, Archie got me
a lovely box of--

21:36.294 --> 21:41.331
we all give ourselves kind of
personal items, Mrs. Jefferson.
We don't talk about them.

21:41.399 --> 21:44.834
Come on, Louise.
I'll show you
what Archie gave me.

21:44.903 --> 21:47.905
Now don't do that, Edith.
Oh, geez.

21:47.972 --> 21:50.874
What's the matter, bunker?
You don't look too good.

21:50.942 --> 21:54.278
What do you mean?
I feel fine.
I feel just fine.

21:54.345 --> 21:57.014
But, while we're
on the subject of looks,

21:57.081 --> 22:00.951
if you're gonna play
Santa claus, Santa claus
was white and so was his beard.

22:01.019 --> 22:02.852
Told you he'd say that,
Uncle Henry.

22:02.921 --> 22:07.157
That's ridiculous.
I'd look silly
with a white beard.

22:07.225 --> 22:11.128
And who said Santa claus
was white?

22:11.195 --> 22:15.365
Come on, now.
I had the same argument
with you about Jesus.

22:17.701 --> 22:20.037
I hate to go over
old ground again,

22:20.104 --> 22:23.540
but the fact is,
Jesus is white
and so is Santa claus.

22:23.607 --> 22:25.708
Yeah? Let me tell you
something, bunker.
Yeah.

22:25.776 --> 22:31.415
When I was a kid on Christmas
Eve, the guy that used to
fill my stocking was black.

22:31.482 --> 22:33.650
- Let me tell you something--
- we ought to get going.

22:33.717 --> 22:36.453
You know the kids
down at the center, Uncle Henry.
Let's go, ma.

22:36.520 --> 22:39.022
<i>Hey, Lionel,</i>
<i>can we go with you?</i>
<i>Yeah, sure. Come on.</i>

22:39.090 --> 22:41.091
Oh, great.
Ma, you don't mind,
do you? We won't be long.

22:41.159 --> 22:44.328
No. Go right ahead.
Have a good time.

22:44.395 --> 22:48.065
Thank you, Louise.
Merry Christmas.

22:48.132 --> 22:51.634
Hey, bunker.
Peace.

22:53.304 --> 22:55.638
Oh, geez.

23:03.247 --> 23:07.250
Oh, Archie,
wasn't that nice?

23:07.318 --> 23:11.488
Nice? What do you mean nice?
What's nice about it?

23:11.555 --> 23:15.225
Guy comes into my house
dressed up like
a famous white person.

23:20.064 --> 23:22.399
Sits in my chair.

23:22.467 --> 23:26.970
Then he goes out
on Christmas day making
a pinko sign like that.

23:27.038 --> 23:31.174
I didn't know peace
was pinko.

23:31.242 --> 23:35.412
Aw, Edith. Listen, listen.
I wanted to tell you something.

23:35.480 --> 23:37.981
What is it, Archie?

23:38.049 --> 23:41.051
Well, it was about
that thing before--

23:41.119 --> 23:45.955
you want to thank me
for understanding about
your Christmas bonus, don't you?

23:46.024 --> 23:49.359
Why don't you never wait
for me to tell you nothing?

23:51.362 --> 23:54.364
I want to thank you
for understanding about
my Christmas bonus.

23:56.800 --> 24:01.304
See, I didn't want you
to think maybe I got the bonus
and blew it on something else,

24:01.372 --> 24:04.641
or maybe I was like
too stingy to spend it,
you know?

24:04.708 --> 24:08.378
Oh, I never thought that,
Archie.

24:08.446 --> 24:11.848
I guessed that you didn't get
your bonus this year...

24:11.916 --> 24:15.052
Because of that mistake
you made down at the plant.

24:16.887 --> 24:19.056
- You guessed that, huh?
- Well, yeah.

24:19.123 --> 24:24.794
I figured that when you sent
that shipment to London, england
instead of London, Ontario...

24:24.862 --> 24:28.265
They kept your Christmas bonus
as a fine.

24:30.268 --> 24:34.404
Yeah, see, they kept
my Christmas bonus as a fine.

24:35.739 --> 24:38.208
Thank you
for telling me, Archie.

24:40.911 --> 24:42.845
[ Sighs ]

24:44.382 --> 24:49.619
Well, I guess it ain't such
a bad Christmas after all, huh?

24:55.893 --> 24:58.895
Hi, mom.
Hi.
Did you have a good time?

24:58.963 --> 25:02.132
Oh, yeah. It was great.
There must've been
200 kids down there.

25:02.200 --> 25:05.702
Oh. Upstairs.
Yeah.
Where's daddy?

25:05.769 --> 25:09.939
Is he in a better mood?
